      "memo": "AGI race pressure is existential because the first to achieve aligned AGI may gain decisive strategic advantage while misaligned AGI threatens survival.",
      "detail": "Existential race pressure means actors perceive AGI as determining national and potentially civilizational survival outcomes. This pressure drives acceleration beyond any rational safety calculus because the alternative is perceived as worse than the risk. The race dynamic creates a collective action problem where individually rational choices produce collectively catastrophic outcomes. Existential pressure is the defining strategic dynamic of AGI development that makes governance so difficult."
    },
