      "detail": "National project structure means AGI development is directed by sovereign authority rather than left to market forces alone. This involves dedicated funding at the hundreds-of-billions scale, cross-agency coordination, and industrial policy alignment. The national project structure reflects the recognition that AGI is too consequential for purely private development governance. National direction enables the security, governance, and accountability structures that private development alone cannot provide."
    },
