      "value": "Enforced regime",
      "memo": "AGI requires an enforced nonproliferation regime with international inspection, technology controls, and sanctions analogous to nuclear weapons governance frameworks.",
      "detail": "Enforced regime means AGI nonproliferation is backed by inspection authority, technology denial mechanisms, and international enforcement powers. This goes beyond voluntary norms or industry self-regulation to binding international agreements with verification procedures. The nuclear nonproliferation model provides the closest precedent though AGI presents unique verification challenges. Enforced nonproliferation is the international governance mechanism necessary to prevent catastrophic proliferation of superhuman capability."
    },
