      "detail": "Structural pricing means AGI development costs are set by strategic investment decisions at the national and institutional level. The hundreds of billions required for frontier training infrastructure transcend normal commercial pricing mechanisms entirely. Input costs include not just compute but facility construction, power infrastructure, and cleared personnel at unprecedented scale. Structural pricing reflects that AGI development is closer to the Manhattan Project than to commercial software development."
    },
